rComments: I find attendance is important, mostly for lectures and class presentations as she gives good extra insight but all you need to know for tests are on her slides. She is passionate about what she teaches and you can see it - a good thing. But she is a hard grader, so use proper grammar of course, be creative (she likes that for papers)!

Hard marker. Check your grammar thoroughly! Once you're not her student anymore, she doesn't really care to keep in touch with you. Most of the students from my class with her didn't like her. We basically taught each other through presentations and she just watched...... Wouldn't take another one with her
She is a very good professor, but she does demand a lot from her students.  Don't take one of her courses unless you intend to work hard and take it seriously.
Not a bad teacher if you like history and litterature... that's what all the essay topics are about. this is a grammar course, while she puts mostly hisory questions on the tests. otherwise, ok.
Both are very interesting couses.  She is into what she teaches.
